author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
President Trump’s personal grievances with Ukraine’s Volodymyr Zelensky date back to his first term in office. WSJ’s chief foreign-affairs correspondent Yaroslav Trofimov explains the history of the long-simmering tensions between the two leaders.
